<title>USA: Western Resources files suit vs ADT.</title>
<headline>Western Resources files suit vs ADT.</headline>
<dateline>TOPEKA, Kan. 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Western Resources Inc said Wednesday it filed a lawsuit against ADT Ltd in the Supreme Court of Bermuda alleging Tyco International Ltd's proposed acquisition of ADT denies Western Resources and other ADT shareholders their appraisal rights.</p>
<p>The lawsuit seeks an order requiring Tyco's acquisition of ADT be structured to provide appraisal rights to ADT shareholders, the company said.  </p>
<p>Western Resources said the rights, which give shareholders the right to be paid &quot;fair value of their shares&quot; in cash, are valuable to the Tyco/ADT transaction because the value of it depends on Tyco's stock price.</p>
<p>Tyco's share price has fluctuated considerably since the merger agreement, Western Resources said.</p>
<p>ADT was not immediately available for comment.</p>
<p>((--Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
